Key Match Events: Suryakumar Yadav won the Player-of-the-Match award for his 51* off 25 balls.
Arshdeep Singh's bouncer dismissed Logan van Beek and his yorker dismissed Fred Klaassen.
Bhuvneshwar Kumar took the wicket of Scott Edwards.
Mohammed Shami dismissed Tim Pringle with a catch by Virat Kohli.
R Ashwin took two wickets, dismissing Colin Ackermann and Tom Cooper.
Axar Patel took the wicket of Bas de Leede.
Paul van Meekeren dismissed KL Rahul.
Pre-Game Insights: Rohit Sharma expected the pitch at SCG to be 'a touch slower' than the one India played Pakistan on at the MCG.
No changes for either team. India stuck with the two-fingerspinner combination, with Yuzvendra Chahal continuing to sit out. No game for Harshal Patel either.
Netherlands captain Scott Edwards spoke about the prospect of facing India, describing it as 'pretty surreal'.
Post-Match Reflections: Suryakumar Yadav expressed that he was just trying to express himself when he went in to bat and that the message was clear to get 8-10 runs an over to ensure a total for the bowlers to defend.
Miscellaneous Highlights: India moved to the top of the Group 2 table with a healthy NRR of 1.425.
The match was played at the Sydney Cricket Ground (SCG).
